x4freetext: Three targets of 124Sn having thicknesses 3.3, 1.7 and
3.2 mg/cm2 used for offline gamma measurement.
Four targets of 159Tb having thicknesses 1.7-1.9 mg/cm2
Two Compton suppressed clover detectors were
placed at a distance of 25 cm from the target center,
one at 125 deg, for absolute cross-section estimation
One Si surface barrier detector of thickness
500 um was placed at 30 deg to monitor Rutherford
The off-line gamma-ray counting was done using
HPGe detector. The energy calibration and efficiency
of the detector were measured by calibrated radioactive
The beam energies were corrected for the loss at half
